<task id="GUID-BED80320-70E5-47C4-9530-CC26073D469D" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title id="GUID-71E6E7FF-D420-465A-9CFA-86F8BA5BE094">Scheduled Report</title>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p>By configuring the <uicontrol>Scheduled Report</uicontrol>, users can receive a list
                of all reports that automatically generate on a user-defined schedule. The
                    <uicontrol>Scheduled Report</uicontrol> screen also provides basic information
                about previously configured schedules and recipients, as well as allows users to
                enable and disable sending scheduled reports</p>
            <note id="note_t5h_dgv_nvb">
                <p>Only <ph conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SPLM_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"
                        >OFFICIAL_PRODUCT_NAME</ph> supports this function.</p>
            </note>
        </context>
        <steps id="steps_pt3_g3m_m5b">
            <step>
                <cmd>Go to <menucascade>
                        <uicontrol>Administration</uicontrol>
                        <uicontrol>Scheduled Report</uicontrol>
                    </menucascade>.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Toggle on <uicontrol>Send scheduled reports</uicontrol>.</cmd>
                <info>
                    <note id="note_hsd_fbx_nvb">
                        <p>By default, the <uicontrol>Scheduled Report</uicontrol> is disabled.</p>
                    </note>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Three available settings appear on the <uicontrol>Scheduled Report</uicontrol>
                    screen.</cmd>
                <info>
                    <table frame="all" id="table_uv2_kbx_nvb">
                        <tgroup cols="2">
                            <colspec colname="c1" colnum="1" colwidth="1*"/>
                            <colspec colname="c2" colnum="2" colwidth="4*"/>
                            <thead>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>
                                        <p>Settings</p>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry>
                                        <p>Description</p>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>
                                        <p><b>Report content</b></p>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry>
                                        <p>Event Type:<ul id="ul_ywy_qbx_nvb">
                                                <li>
                                                  <p><ph
                                                  conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SPLM_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"
                                                  >OFFICIAL_PRODUCT_NAME</ph> Blocked Event
                                                  History</p>
                                                </li>
                                                <li>
                                                  <p><ph
                                                  conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SPLM_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"
                                                  >OFFICIAL_PRODUCT_NAME</ph> Top 10 Endpoints with
                                                  Blocked Events</p>
                                                </li>
                                                <li>
                                                  <p><ph
                                                  conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SPLM_ALTERNATIVE_NAME"
                                                  >OFFICIAL_PRODUCT_NAME</ph> Top 10 Blocked
                                                  Files</p>
                                                </li>
                                            </ul></p>
                                        <p>Time Period: A drop-down menu for users to choose
                                            preferred time period during which the above-mentioned
                                            events occur</p>
                                        <ul id="ul_ag5_5bx_nvb">
                                            <li>
                                                <p>Last 7 days</p>
                                            </li>
                                            <li>
                                                <p>Last 14 days</p>
                                            </li>
                                            <li>
                                                <p>Last 30 days</p>
                                            </li>
                                            <li>
                                                <p>Last 3 months</p>
                                            </li>
                                            <li>
                                                <p>Last 6 months</p>
                                            </li>
                                        </ul>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>
                                        <p><b>Schedule</b></p>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry>
                                        <p>Set the frequency and start time for the scheduled
                                            reports on a daily, weekly, or monthly basis.</p>
                                        <note type="note" id="note_tj1_fdx_nvb">
                                            <p>It is advisable NOT to select the date 29th, 30th, or
                                                31st for monthly update frequency. This helps
                                                prevent the system from bypassing the update in the
                                                month that does not contain the date 29th, 30th, or
                                                31st.</p>
                                        </note>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                                <row>
                                    <entry>
                                        <p><b>Recipients</b></p>
                                    </entry>
                                    <entry>
                                        <p>A valid email address is required for specifying the
                                            report recipient.</p>
                                        <note id="note_jp2_ydx_nvb">
                                            <p>When entering muiltiple email addresses, be sure to
                                                use the semicolon character to separate them.</p>
                                        </note>
                                    </entry>
                                </row>
                            </tbody>
                        </tgroup>
                    </table>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click <uicontrol>Save</uicontrol> to save the settings.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
